VENEZUELAN EQUINE ENCEPHALITIS, EQUINE - COLOMBIA (02): (CORDOBA)
*****************************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
<http://www.promedmail.org>
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
<http://www.isid.org>

Date: Tue 10 Aug 2010
Source: El Meridiano de Cordoba [in Spanish, trans. Corr.SB, edited]
<http://www.elmeridianodecordoba.com.co/index.php?option=com_content&view=article&id=38548>


Two cases of Venezuelan equine encephalitis were detected in Monteria and
Puerto Esondido [department (state or province equivalent) of Cordoba].
Confirmation was made by ICA [Instituto Colombiano Agropecuario --
Colombian Agricultural Institute, where the central veterinary diagnostic
laboratory is located. - Mod.TY] after laboratory tests for zoonoses were
carried out on samples taken from the animals.

The cases occurred specifically in the Todos Pensamos locality of the Nueva
Esperanza settlement in Monteria municipality and in the El Palmar locality
in the municipality of Puerto Escondido.

The Public Health sector of the departmental Secretariat of Health
commissioned a group of epidemiologists and bacteriologists
[microbiologists] to carry out field studies in the area in order to
initiate follow up, surveillance, and epidemiological research activities.
Similarly, to protect the community, the alert status will be maintained,
and prevention measures will be taken jointly between Public Health,
Environmental Health and Emergencies, and Disaster Prevention agencies, and
all health providers of the areas where the cases were reported.

[byline: Julia Arroyo Munoz]

